    "label": {
        "none": [
            "Schist Buddha Triad (year 5)"
        ]
    },
    "summary": {
        "none": [
            "Depicts the Buddha seated on a lotus-throne under a leafy canopy flanked by Bodhisattvas and attended by deities above his shoulders. To the Buddha’s right is most likely the bodhisattva Maitreya. The bodhisattva on the left is commonly identified as Avalokiteshvara. Floating above the Buddha’s shoulders are the Indic gods Brahma (on the Buddha’s right), and Indra (on the left). Recent scholarship associates this scene with Buddha-fields, a concept found in Mahayana Buddhism. The inscription on the pedestal states that the object was a donation made by Budhanada and commissioned to honour his deceased parents."
        ]
    },
